*****
[2] Canada
Date: Tue 1 Sep 2020
Source: My Yellow Knife Now [edited]
https://www.myyellowknifenow.com/49992/457-canadian-salmonella-cases-linked-to-american-onions/


Canada's Public Health Agency is warning onions from the USA may bring more than tears to your eyes. There have now been over 457 Canadians who have fallen ill from salmonellosis linked to onions imported from the States, 78 more diagnosed in the last 10 days. There have been 67 people admitted to the hospital and one person has died although the death has not been directly linked to _Salmonella_.

The agency is warning Canadians not to buy any onions imported from the USA and instead stick with Canadian produce, which has not been named in the warning.

